&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Trustpilot, we&#39;re on an incredible journey. We&#39;re a profitable, high-growth FTSE-250 company with a big vision: to become the universal symbol of trust. We run the world&#39;s largest open customer review platform, and while we&#39;ve come a long way, there&#39;s still so much exciting work to do. Come join us at the heart of trust!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Trustpilot’s growth has been exponential - from a successful IPO to building out new teams, we never stop working hard to fulfill our mission to create better experiences for everyone through our platform. But to do that, we need data! That’s where Analytics comes in - you’ll help us measure, uncover insights, and predict, to get data everywhere in Trustpilot. We’ve built a world-class analytics team that spans two continents and four cities - are you ready to join a fun, diverse global team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trustpilot is on a mission to create better experiences for everyone through our platform. But to do that, we need to protect the integrity of our community and deeply understand how our consumers perceive trust. We’ve built a world-class analytics team that spans continents and cities - and now, we’re looking for a data analyst to support our regulatory duty and protect trust for our platform and consumers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team is the guardian of our platform. They use data to stay one step ahead of bad actors, working with the teams that build the models and detection systems that identify fake reviews and ensure Trustpilot remains a universal symbol of integrity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a huge part of what we do at Trustpilot - it’s in the name! We need to ensure that the content on our platform is real content from real people. That means eliminating scam and spam, and identifying fraudulent behavior. We have several cross functional teams devoted to Trust. You’ll be tightly aligned to their goals, helping teams such as Content Integrity, Legal &amp;amp; Compliance, Corporate Comms &amp;amp; Investor Relations, Fraud &amp;amp; Investigations to investigate requests on fraudulent activity, prepare various reports including core publicly shared company and regulatory reports.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Data Analyst at Trustpilot, you will collaborate with Trusties in our Trust, Comms and Marketing teams and spend your time digging through our data to provide them with data-driven insights, as well as analytics and dashboards/reporting. You’re keen to help them use data to answer their toughest questions, and you can proactively identify areas that need a little data support. You’ll be an internal data consultant, with loads of amazing data in our data warehouse at your fingertips, working with analytical tools including BigQuery and Looker.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What you’ll be doing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the main contact point for all regulatory and compliance reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivering expert analytics and insights to different parts of the business, through both workstream-driven initiatives and ad-hoc inquiries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building data sets and dashboards that support our Trust data integrity and auditability requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Picking the right solution for the problem you’ve got, from your arsenal of analytical tools and methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with the Comms, Investor Relations, Marketing, Compliance or Trust teams to understand their data requests and their goals to deliver awesome solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Presenting and promoting your work to the wider business, to enable data-informed decision making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scoping and documenting projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardising

